---
const title = "Exercises";
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title={title}>
  <h2>CSS Animation</h2>

  <p>
    Reflecting back on Project 2, choose the hero on your homepage or another
    element that you can animate using either a CSS Keyframe animation. or CSS
    transitions. For inspiration, consider something like the hero file
    attached.
  </p>
  <p>When posting to D2L, Make sure to explain what you have changed.</p>

  <p>
    Using the lesson notes under the <a
      href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}lessons/animation/`}>Animation</a
    > section, Create a CSS animation that either promotes your <a
      href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}projects/project-2/`}>Project 2</a
    > news site or can reside as a feature within it. The dimensions are up to you.
  </p>
  <p>
    It could be an animation that builds and completes, <a
      href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}lessons/animation/hero`}
      target="_blank">like this example</a
    >, or something that loops.
  </p>

  <p><strong>Step 1:</strong> Design a layout in Figma.</p>
  <p><strong>Step 2:</strong> Build the layout in HTML and CSS.</p>
  <p><strong>Step 3:</strong> Animate with CSS.</p>
</Layout>
